{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to take you back basically to my hometown,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and to a picture of my hometown of the week"},{"time":5000,"text":"that \"Emergence\" came out."},{"time":7000,"text":"And it's a picture we've seen several times."},{"time":15000,"text":"Basically, \"Emergence\" was published on 9/11."},{"time":18000,"text":"I live right there in the West Village,"},{"time":23000,"text":"so the plume was luckily blowing west, away from us."},{"time":28000,"text":"We had a two-and-a-half-day-old baby in the house that was ours --"},{"time":35000,"text":"we hadn't taken it from somebody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"And one of the thoughts that I had dealing with these two separate emergences"},{"time":46000,"text":"of a book and a baby, and having this event happen so close --"},{"time":50000,"text":"that my first thought, when I was still kind of in the apartment looking out at it all"},{"time":54000,"text":"or walking out on the street and looking out on it just in front of our building,"},{"time":57000,"text":"was that I'd made a terrible miscalculation in the book that I'd just written."},{"time":62000,"text":"Because so much of that book was a celebration of the power"},{"time":66000,"text":"and creative potential of density, of largely urban density,"},{"time":70000,"text":"of connecting people and putting them together in one place,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and putting them on sidewalks together and having them share ideas"},{"time":76000,"text":"and share physical space together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"And it seemed to me looking at that -- that tower burning and then falling,"},{"time":81000,"text":"those towers burning and falling -- that in fact, one of the lessons"},{"time":83000,"text":"here was that density kills."},{"time":85000,"text":"And that of all the technologies that were exploited"},{"time":88000,"text":"to make that carnage come into being,"},{"time":93000,"text":"probably the single group of technologies that cost the most lives"},{"time":99000,"text":"were those that enable 50,000 people to live in two buildings"},{"time":103000,"text":"110 stories above the ground."},{"time":105000,"text":"If they hadn't been crowded --"},{"time":107000,"text":"you compare the loss of life at the Pentagon to the Twin Towers,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and you can see that very powerfully."},{"time":112000,"text":"And so I started to think, well, you know, density, density --"},{"time":115000,"text":"I'm not sure if, you know, this was the right call."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"And I kind of ruminated on that for a couple of days."},{"time":122000,"text":"And then about two days later, the wind started to change a little bit,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and you could sense that the air was not healthy."},{"time":129000,"text":"And so even though there were no cars still in the West Village"},{"time":133000,"text":"where we lived, my wife sent me out to buy a, you know,"},{"time":136000,"text":"a large air filter at the Bed Bath and Beyond,"},{"time":140000,"text":"which was located about 20 blocks away, north."},{"time":143000,"text":"And so I went out."},{"time":145000,"text":"And obviously I'm physically a very strong person, as you can tell -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":149000,"text":"so I wasn't worried about carrying this thing 20 blocks."},{"time":152000,"text":"And I walked out, and this really miraculous thing happened to me"},{"time":156000,"text":"as I was walking north to buy this air filter,"},{"time":159000,"text":"which was that the streets were completely alive with people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"There was an incredible -- it was, you know, a beautiful day,"},{"time":167000,"text":"as it was for about a week after,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and the West Village had never seemed more lively."},{"time":172000,"text":"I walked up along Hudson Street --"},{"time":174000,"text":"where Jane Jacobs had lived and written her great book"},{"time":176000,"text":"that so influenced what I was writing in \"Emergence\" --"},{"time":178000,"text":"past the White Horse Tavern,"},{"time":180000,"text":"that great old bar where Dylan Thomas drank himself to death,"},{"time":183000,"text":"and the Bleecker Street playground was filled with kids."},{"time":186000,"text":"And all the people who lived in the neighborhood,"},{"time":188000,"text":"who owned restaurants and bars in the neighborhood,"},{"time":190000,"text":"were all out there -- had them all open."},{"time":192000,"text":"People were out."},{"time":194000,"text":"There were no cars, so it seemed even better, in some ways."},{"time":196000,"text":"And it was a beautiful urban day,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and the incredible thing about it was that the city was working."},{"time":203000,"text":"The city was there."},{"time":205000,"text":"All the things that make a great city successful"},{"time":207000,"text":"and all the things that make a great city stimulating --"},{"time":209000,"text":"they were all on display there on those streets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"And I thought, well, this is the power of a city."},{"time":215000,"text":"I mean, the power of the city --"},{"time":217000,"text":"we talked about cities as being centralized in space,"},{"time":219000,"text":"but what makes them so strong most of the time"},{"time":221000,"text":"is they're decentralized in function."},{"time":223000,"text":"They don't have a center executive branch that you can take out"},{"time":225000,"text":"and cause the whole thing to fail."},{"time":227000,"text":"If they did, it probably was right there at Ground Zero."},{"time":230000,"text":"I mean, you know, the emergency bunker was right there,"},{"time":232000,"text":"was destroyed by the attacks,"},{"time":234000,"text":"and obviously the damage done to the building and the lives."},{"time":236000,"text":"But nonetheless, just 20 blocks north, two days later,"},{"time":240000,"text":"the city had never looked more alive."},{"time":243000,"text":"If you'd gone into the minds of the people,"},{"time":245000,"text":"well, you would have seen a lot of trauma,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and you would have seen a lot of heartache,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and you would have seen a lot of things that would take a long time to recover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"But the system itself of this city was thriving."},{"time":255000,"text":"So I took heart in seeing that."},{"time":258000,"text":"So I wanted to talk a little bit about the reasons why that works so well,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and how some of those reasons kind of map"},{"time":266000,"text":"on to where the Web is going right now."},{"time":269000,"text":"The question that I found myself asking to people"},{"time":271000,"text":"when I was talking about the book afterwards is --"},{"time":273000,"text":"when you've talked about emergent behavior,"},{"time":275000,"text":"when you've talked about collective intelligence,"},{"time":277000,"text":"the best way to get people to kind of wrap their heads around that"},{"time":279000,"text":"is to ask, who builds a neighborhood?"},{"time":282000,"text":"Who decides that Soho should have this personality"},{"time":285000,"text":"and that the Latin Quarter should have this personality?"},{"time":287000,"text":"Well, there are some kind of executive decisions,"},{"time":289000,"text":"but mostly the answer is -- everybody and nobody."},{"time":291000,"text":"Everybody contributes a little bit."},{"time":293000,"text":"No single person is really the ultimate actor"},{"time":297000,"text":"behind the personality of a neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Same thing to the question of, who was keeping the streets alive"},{"time":302000,"text":"post-9/11 in my neighborhood?"},{"time":304000,"text":"Well, it was the whole city."},{"time":306000,"text":"The whole system kind of working on it,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and everybody contributing a small little part."},{"time":310000,"text":"And this is increasingly what we're starting to see on the Web"},{"time":313000,"text":"in a bunch of interesting ways --"},{"time":315000,"text":"most of which weren't around, actually,"},{"time":317000,"text":"except in very experimental things,"},{"time":319000,"text":"when I was writing \"Emergence\" and when the book came out."},{"time":321000,"text":"So it's been a very optimistic time, I think,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and I want to just talk about a few of those things."},{"time":325000,"text":"I think that there is effectively a new kind of model of interactivity"},{"time":329000,"text":"that's starting to emerge online right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"And the old one looked like this."},{"time":336000,"text":"This is not the future King of England, although it looks like it."},{"time":340000,"text":"It's some guy, it's a GeoCities homepage of some guy that I found online"},{"time":343000,"text":"who's interested, if you look at the bottom, in soccer and Jesus"},{"time":346000,"text":"and Garth Brooks and Clint Beckham and \"my hometown\" -- those are his links."},{"time":349000,"text":"But nothing really says"},{"time":351000,"text":"this model of interactivity -- which was so exciting and captures the real,"},{"time":355000,"text":"the Web Zeitgeist of 1995 -- than"},{"time":358000,"text":"\"Click here for a picture of my dog.\""},{"time":360000,"text":"That is -- you know, there's no sentence"},{"time":362000,"text":"that kind of conjures up that period better than that, I think,"},{"time":366000,"text":"which is that you suddenly have the power to put up a picture of your dog"},{"time":369000,"text":"and link to it, and somebody reading the page"},{"time":372000,"text":"has the power to click on that link or not click on that link."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"And, you know, I don't want to belittle that. That, in a sense --"},{"time":378000,"text":"to reference what Jeff was talking about yesterday --"},{"time":381000,"text":"that was, in a sense, the kind of interface electricity that"},{"time":383000,"text":"powered a lot of the explosion of interest in the Web:"},{"time":386000,"text":"that you could put up a link, and somebody could click on it,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and it could take you anywhere you wanted to go."},{"time":390000,"text":"But it's still a very one-to-one kind of relationship."},{"time":392000,"text":"There's one person putting up the link, and there's another person"},{"time":394000,"text":"on the other end trying to decide whether to click on it or not."},{"time":399000,"text":"The new model is much more like this,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and we've already seen a couple of references to this."},{"time":403000,"text":"This is what happens when you search \"Steven Johnson\" on Google."},{"time":407000,"text":"About two months ago, I had the great breakthrough --"},{"time":411000,"text":"one of my great, kind of shining achievements --"},{"time":414000,"text":"which is that my website finally became a top result for \"Steven Johnson.\""},{"time":417000,"text":"There's some theoretical physicist at MIT named Steven Johnson"},{"time":423000,"text":"who has dropped two spots, I'm happy to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"And, you know, I mean, I'll look at a couple of things like this,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but Google is obviously the greatest technology ever invented for navel gazing."},{"time":435000,"text":"It's just that there are so many other people in your navel when you gaze."},{"time":438000,"text":"Because effectively, what's happening here,"},{"time":443000,"text":"what's creating this page, obviously -- and we all know this,"},{"time":445000,"text":"but it's worth just thinking about it --"},{"time":447000,"text":"is not some person deciding that I am the number one answer for Steven Johnson,"},{"time":451000,"text":"but rather somehow the entire web of people"},{"time":455000,"text":"putting up pages and deciding to link to my page or not link to it,"},{"time":458000,"text":"and Google just sitting there and running the numbers."},{"time":461000,"text":"So there's this collective decision-making that's going on."},{"time":465000,"text":"This page is effectively, collectively authored by the Web,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and Google is just helping us"},{"time":470000,"text":"kind of to put the authorship in one kind of coherent place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"Now, they're more innovative -- well, Google's pretty innovative --"},{"time":476000,"text":"but there are some new twists on this."},{"time":479000,"text":"There's this incredibly interesting new site -- Technorati --"},{"time":481000,"text":"that's filled with lots of little widgets that are expanding on these."},{"time":485000,"text":"And these are looking in the blog world and the world of weblogs."},{"time":489000,"text":"He's analyzed basically all the weblogs out there that he's tracking."},{"time":493000,"text":"And he's tracking how many other weblogs linked to those weblogs,"},{"time":496000,"text":"and so you have kind of an authority --"},{"time":498000,"text":"a weblog that has a lot of links to it"},{"time":500000,"text":"is more authoritative than a weblog that has few links to it."},{"time":505000,"text":"And so at any given time, on any given page on the Web, actually,"},{"time":507000,"text":"you can say, what does the weblog community think about this page?"},{"time":510000,"text":"And you can get a list."},{"time":512000,"text":"This is what they think about my site; it's ranked by blog authority."},{"time":515000,"text":"You can also rank it by the latest posts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"So when I was talking in \"Emergence,\""},{"time":520000,"text":"I talked about the limitations of the one-way linking architecture"},{"time":522000,"text":"that, basically, you could link to somebody else"},{"time":524000,"text":"but they wouldn't necessarily know that you were pointing to them."},{"time":526000,"text":"And that was one of the reasons why the web"},{"time":529000,"text":"wasn't quite as emergent as it could be"},{"time":531000,"text":"because you needed two-way linking, you needed that kind of feedback mechanism"},{"time":533000,"text":"to be able to really do interesting things."},{"time":535000,"text":"Well, something like Technorati is supplying that."},{"time":538000,"text":"Now what's interesting here is that this is a quote from Dave Weinberger,"},{"time":541000,"text":"where he talks about everything being purposive in the Web --"},{"time":545000,"text":"there's nothing artificial."},{"time":547000,"text":"He has this line where he says, you know, you're going to put up a link there,"},{"time":549000,"text":"if you see a link, somebody decided to put it there."},{"time":552000,"text":"And he says, the link to one site didn't just grow on the other page \"like a tree fungus.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"And in fact, I think that's not entirely true anymore."},{"time":560000,"text":"I could put up a feed of all those links generated by Technorati"},{"time":564000,"text":"on the right-hand side of my page,"},{"time":566000,"text":"and they would change as the overall ecology of the Web changes."},{"time":569000,"text":"That little list there would change."},{"time":571000,"text":"I wouldn't really be directly in control of it."},{"time":573000,"text":"So it's much closer, in a way, to a data fungus, in a sense,"},{"time":576000,"text":"wrapped around that page, than it is to a deliberate link that I've placed there."},{"time":582000,"text":"Now, what you're having here is basically a global brain"},{"time":585000,"text":"that you're able to do lots of kind of experiments on to see what it's thinking."},{"time":588000,"text":"And there are all these interesting tools."},{"time":590000,"text":"Google does the Google Zeitgeist,"},{"time":592000,"text":"which looks at search requests to test what's going on, what people are interested in,"},{"time":597000,"text":"and they publish it with lots of fun graphs."},{"time":599000,"text":"And I'm saying a lot of nice things about Google,"},{"time":601000,"text":"so I'll be I'll be saying one little critical thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"There's a problem with the Google Zeitgeist,"},{"time":604000,"text":"which is it often comes back with news that a lot of people are searching"},{"time":608000,"text":"for Britney Spears pictures, which is not necessarily news."},{"time":612000,"text":"The Columbia blows up, suddenly there are a lot of searches on Columbia."},{"time":616000,"text":"Well, you know, we should expect to see that."},{"time":618000,"text":"That's not necessarily something we didn't know already."},{"time":620000,"text":"So the key thing in terms of these new tools"},{"time":622000,"text":"that are kind of plumbing the depths of the global brain,"},{"time":625000,"text":"that are sending kind of trace dyes through that whole bloodstream --"},{"time":629000,"text":"the question is, are you finding out something new?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"And one of the things that I experimented with is this thing called Google Share"},{"time":634000,"text":"which is basically, you take an abstract term,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and you search Google for that term,"},{"time":641000,"text":"and then you search the results that you get back for somebody's name."},{"time":644000,"text":"So basically, the number of pages that mention this term,"},{"time":648000,"text":"that also mention this page, the percentage of those pages"},{"time":651000,"text":"is that person's Google Share of that term."},{"time":653000,"text":"So you can do kind of interesting contests."},{"time":655000,"text":"Like for instance, this is a Google Share of the TED Conference."},{"time":659000,"text":"So Richard Saul Wurman"},{"time":662000,"text":"has about a 15 percent Google Share of the TED conference."},{"time":666000,"text":"Our good friend Chris has about a six percent -- but with a bullet, I might add."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"But the interesting thing is, you can broaden the search a little bit."},{"time":676000,"text":"And it turns out, actually, that 42 percent is the Mola mola fish."},{"time":679000,"text":"I had no idea."},{"time":681000,"text":"No, that's not true."},{"time":682000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":685000,"text":"I made that up because I just wanted to put up a slide"},{"time":687000,"text":"of the Mola mola fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"I also did -- and I don't want to start a little fight in the next panel --"},{"time":694000,"text":"but I did a Google Share analysis of evolution and natural selection."},{"time":697000,"text":"So right here -- now this is a big category, you have smaller percentages,"},{"time":702000,"text":"so this is 0.7 percent -- Dan Dennett, who'll be speaking shortly."},{"time":707000,"text":"Right below him, 0.5 percent, Steven Pinker."},{"time":712000,"text":"So Dennett's in the lead a little bit there."},{"time":714000,"text":"But what's interesting is you can then broaden the search"},{"time":716000,"text":"and actually see interesting things and get a sense of what else is out there."},{"time":720000,"text":"So Gary Bauer is not too far behind --"},{"time":723000,"text":"has slightly different theories about evolution and natural selection."},{"time":728000,"text":"And right behind him is L. Ron Hubbard. So --"},{"time":731000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":733000,"text":"you can see we're in the ascot, which is always good."},{"time":735000,"text":"And by the way, Chris, that would've been a really good panel,"},{"time":737000,"text":"I think, right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"Hubbard apparently started to reach, but besides that,"},{"time":745000,"text":"I think it would be good next year."},{"time":747000,"text":"Another quick thing -- this is a slightly different thing,"},{"time":749000,"text":"but this analysis some of you may have seen."},{"time":751000,"text":"It just came out. This is bursty words,"},{"time":753000,"text":"looking at the historical record of State of the Union Addresses."},{"time":758000,"text":"So these are words that suddenly start to appear out of nowhere,"},{"time":762000,"text":"so they're kind of, you know, memes that start taking off,"},{"time":764000,"text":"that didn't have a lot of historical precedent before."},{"time":767000,"text":"So the first one is -- these are the bursty words around 1860s --"},{"time":770000,"text":"slaves, emancipation, slavery, rebellion, Kansas."},{"time":773000,"text":"That's Britney Spears. I mean, you know, OK, interesting."},{"time":775000,"text":"They're talking about slavery in 1860."},{"time":777000,"text":"1935 -- relief, depression, recovery banks."},{"time":780000,"text":"And OK, I didn't learn anything new there as well -- that's pretty obvious."},{"time":783000,"text":"1985, right at the center of the Reagan years --"},{"time":787000,"text":"that's, we're, there's, we've, it's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"Now, there's one way to interpret this, which is to say that"},{"time":795000,"text":"\"emancipation\" and \"depression\" and \"recovery\" all have a lot of syllables."},{"time":798000,"text":"So you know, you can actually download -- it's hard to remember those."},{"time":803000,"text":"But seriously, actually, what you can see there,"},{"time":805000,"text":"in a way that would be very hard to detect otherwise,"},{"time":807000,"text":"is Reagan reinventing the political language of the country"},{"time":810000,"text":"and shifting to a much more intimate, much more folksy, much more telegenic --"},{"time":814000,"text":"contracting all those verbs."},{"time":816000,"text":"You know, 20 years before it was still, \"Ask not what you can do,\""},{"time":818000,"text":"but with Reagan, it's, \"that's where, there's Nancy and I,\" that kind of language."},{"time":823000,"text":"And so something we kind of knew,"},{"time":826000,"text":"but you didn't actually notice syntactically what he was doing."},{"time":828000,"text":"I'll go very quickly."},{"time":830000,"text":"The question now -- and this is the really interesting question --"},{"time":832000,"text":"is, what kind of higher-level shape is emerging right now"},{"time":836000,"text":"in the overall Web ecosystem -- and particularly in the ecosystem of the blogs"},{"time":840000,"text":"because they are really kind of at the cutting edge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843000,"text":"And I think what happens there will also happen in the wider system."},{"time":845000,"text":"Now there was a very interesting article by Clay Shirky"},{"time":848000,"text":"that got a lot of attention about a month ago,"},{"time":850000,"text":"and this is basically the distribution of links"},{"time":852000,"text":"on the web to all these various different blogs."},{"time":857000,"text":"It follows a power law, so that there are a few extremely well-linked to, popular blogs,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and a long tail of blogs with very few links."},{"time":866000,"text":"So 20 percent of the blogs get 80 percent of the links."},{"time":869000,"text":"Now this is a very interesting thing."},{"time":871000,"text":"It's caused a lot of controversy"},{"time":873000,"text":"because people thought that this was the ultimate kind of one man,"},{"time":875000,"text":"one modem democracy, where anybody can get out there and get their voice heard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"And so the question is, \"Why is this happening?\""},{"time":881000,"text":"It's not being imposed by fiat from above."},{"time":885000,"text":"It's an emergent property of the blogosphere right now."},{"time":888000,"text":"Now, what's great about it is that people are working on --"},{"time":891000,"text":"within seconds of Clay publishing this piece, people started working on changing"},{"time":896000,"text":"the underlying rules of the system so that a different shape would start appearing."},{"time":899000,"text":"And basically, the shape appears"},{"time":901000,"text":"largely because of a kind of a first-mover advantage."},{"time":903000,"text":"if you're the first site there, everybody links to you."},{"time":905000,"text":"If you're the second site there, most people link to you."},{"time":907000,"text":"And so very quickly you can accumulate a bunch of links,"},{"time":910000,"text":"and it makes it more likely for newcomers to link to you in the future,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and then you get this kind of shape."},{"time":914000,"text":"And so what Dave Sifry at Technorati started working on,"},{"time":917000,"text":"literally as Shirky started -- after he published his piece --"},{"time":920000,"text":"was something that basically just gave a new kind of priority to newcomers."},{"time":924000,"text":"And he started looking at interesting newcomers that don't have a lot of links,"},{"time":927000,"text":"that suddenly get a bunch of links in the last 24 hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"So in a sense, bursty weblogs coming from new voices."},{"time":934000,"text":"So he's working on a tool right there that can actually change the overall system."},{"time":939000,"text":"And it creates a kind of planned emergence."},{"time":941000,"text":"You're not totally in control,"},{"time":943000,"text":"but you're changing the underlying rules in interesting ways"},{"time":945000,"text":"because you have an end result which is"},{"time":947000,"text":"maybe a more democratic spread of voices."},{"time":949000,"text":"So the most amazing thing about this -- and I'll end on this note --"},{"time":951000,"text":"is, most emergent systems, most self-organizing systems"},{"time":954000,"text":"are not made up of component parts that are capable of looking at the overall pattern"},{"time":959000,"text":"and changing their behavior based on whether they like the pattern or not."},{"time":963000,"text":"So the most wonderful thing, I think, about this whole debate"},{"time":965000,"text":"about power laws and software that could change it"},{"time":967000,"text":"is the fact that we're having the conversation."},{"time":970000,"text":"I hope it continues here."},{"time":972000,"text":"Thanks a lot."}]}]}